external_knowledge:
'sluggish' refers to operations taking more than 15 units of time;
'minor delay' is considered to be 10 units of time or less;
The question aims to identify devices that are performing poorly in terms of open operation latency in New York.

sql:
SELECT id, timestamp, device_id, network_segment_id, protocol, service, metric_type, location, status, anomaly_detected
FROM network_metrics
WHERE anomaly_detected = 1 AND location = 'New York';

SELECT MAX(bind)
FROM network_metrics
WHERE network_segment_id = 0;

SELECT device_id, network_segment_id, timestamp, metric_type, status, anomaly_detected
FROM network_metrics
WHERE status != 'normal' AND timestamp BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';

SELECT name, location 
FROM devices 
WHERE id > 0;

SELECT location, SUM(id)
FROM network_segments
GROUP BY location;
